      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense, but I'm trying to dig deeper into the actual drivers. when you look at the raw numbers for specific groups, some researchers argue that systemic bias alone doesn't account for the entirety of the gap. how much of this do you think is actually due to innate cultural differences or behavioral patterns within those specific communities vs just the external systemic factors?",
