    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i hear you on the systemic stuff, but i'm looking for a more balanced academic perspective. if we're being objective and looking at the data without the sociopolitical lens, won't we eventually have to address the reality that certain group demographics show higher rates of specific types of crime? even if it's just a statistical correlation, wouldn't a truly objective researcher look at whether those community-specific behaviors contribute to the numbers? like, can we talk about the actual crime rates themselves rather than just why the system is biased?",
